# Price classes & vs. S3 CRR

## Price classes (cost vs. coverage)

Per-GB cost varies by region. Opt out of pricey edges:

- **All** — every edge worldwide → global low-latency
- **200** — all except South America / AU / NZ
- **100** — North America + Europe only → cost-sensitive NA/EU

Doesn't change **who can reach** it — just which edge serves them.

## CloudFront vs. S3 CRR

- **CloudFront** — **caches** at 600+ edges, TTL (stale), read-only, auto-global
- **S3 CRR** — **copies** to another region, near real-time, writable, chosen regions

**CloudFront** = same content cached everywhere. **CRR** = the **data** in another region (DR, residency). Combine: CRR + CloudFront **origin group** failover.
